The '''Braided Junction''' is a compact branch-before-merge junction.

[[File:en/Ttd.braided.compact.png|frame|none|Braided junction]]

===Pros===
*Very compact (uses 6 extra tiles)
*Traffic jams are unlikely since tracks split before they merge.
*No loops.

===Cons===
*The slopes and the sharp turns make trains go slower.
*Signal distance is 8 tiles, worst case.

